.Dd June 10, 2026
.Dt LIBCERROR 3
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm libcerror.h
.Nd Library to support cross-platform C error functions
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In libcerror.h
.Pp
Support functions
.nf
.Ft const char *
.Fo libcerror_get_version
.Fa "void"
.Fc
.fi
.Pp
Error functions
.nf
.Ft void
.Fo libcerror_error_free
.Fa "libcerror_error_t **error"
.Fc
.fi
.nf
.Ft void
.Fo libcerror_error_set
.Fa "libcerror_error_t **error"
.Fa "int error_domain"
.Fa "int error_code"
.Fa "const char *format_string"
.Va ...
.Fc
.fi
.nf
.Ft int
.Fo libcerror_error_matches
.Fa "libcerror_error_t *error"
.Fa "int error_domain"
.Fa "int error_code"
.Fc
.fi
.nf
.Ft int
.Fo libcerror_error_fprint
.Fa "libcerror_error_t *error"
.Fa "FILE *stream"
.Fc
.fi
.nf
.Ft int
.Fo libcerror_error_sprint
.Fa "libcerror_error_t *error"
.Fa "char *string"
.Fa "size_t size"
.Fc
.fi
.nf
.Ft int
.Fo libcerror_error_backtrace_fprint
.Fa "libcerror_error_t *error"
.Fa "FILE *stream"
.Fc
.fi
.nf
.Ft int
.Fo libcerror_error_backtrace_sprint
.Fa "libcerror_error_t *error"
.Fa "char *string"
.Fa "size_t size"
.Fc
.fi
.Pp
System error functions
.nf
.Ft void
.Fo libcerror_system_set_error
.Fa "libcerror_error_t **error"
.Fa "int error_domain"
.Fa "int error_code"
.Fa "uint32_t system_error_code"
.Fa "const char *format_string"
.Va ...
.Fc
.fi
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Fn libcerror_get_version
function is used to retrieve the library version.
.Sh RETURN VALUES
Most of the functions return NULL or \-1 on error, dependent on the return \
type.
For the actual return values see
.In libcerror.h .
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
None
.Sh FILES
None
.Sh SEE ALSO
.In libcerror.h
